article.headline: Mississippi 78, Auburn 59
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. -- Terrico White scored 19 points as Mississippi placed five players in double figures to defeat Auburn 78-59 on Wednesday night. David Huertas scored 16 points and Zach Graham had 11, while Terrance Henry and Malcolm White added 10 apiece for the Rebels (13-9, 4-4 Southeastern Conference). Korvotney Barber led Auburn (13-9, 2-4) with 17 points and 13 rebounds. DeWayne Reed and Frankie Sullivan added 14 and 12 points, respectively. White's pair of dunks highlighted a 21-5 run midway through the first half, building a 46-28 halftime lead for Mississippi. The Rebels led by as many as 22 points in the second half. The Rebels were 27 of 63 from the field (42.9 percent), including 10 of 28 from 3-point range. Mississippi outrebounded the Tigers 42-36 and limited Auburn to 6 of 27 (22.2 percent) from long range.
